<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>soft market • soft sell</xh5><p> <i>soft market—</i>said of a period when sales are few and prices are low: The period of the 1990s is regarded as a <u>soft market</u> for property and casualty insurance.</p><p> <i>soft sell—</i>a subtly persuasive, low-pressure method of selling or advertising: When I say <u>soft sell</u> is the key to this generation, it’s still ultimately about creating loyal customers. <i>Cf.: hard sell</i>—selling or advertising smth. very aggressively and with great eagerness: When it comes to getting children interested in the business, a soft sell is better than a <u>hard sell</u>.</p> </entry>
